<section id="fiche_descriptions">

    
    
    <h3>Obverse</h3>
    
        <p>Second laureate and draped bust (&#039;Bun Head&#039;) of Queen Victoria left, legend around.<br />
<br />
Note: varieties exist</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
                <span id="obverse_lettering" class="lettering">VICTORIA D:G: BRITT:REG:F:D:</span>
    </p>
            
        <p>
        <strong>Unabridged legend:</strong>
                Victoria Dei Gratia Britanniarum Regina Fidei Defensatrix    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Translation:</strong>
                Victoria by the Grace of God Queen of the Britains Defender of the Faith    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=46">Leonard Charles Wyon</a>    </p>
        
    
    <h3>Reverse</h3>
    
        <p>Seated figure of Britannia right with trident in left hand and shield bearing the Union flag in right, sea behind with lighthouse on left and ship on right, denomination around, date in exergue.<br />
<br />
Note: varieties exist</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
        <br />        <span id="reverse_lettering" class="lettering">ONE PENNY<br />
1863</span>
    </p>
            
        
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=46">Leonard Charles Wyon</a>    </p>
        
    
    <h3>Edge</h3>
    
        <p>Plain</p>
        
        
        
        
    
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-original.jpg" target="_blank" class="coin_pic" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="coin_pic">
        <img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-180.jpg"
            srcset="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-100.jpg 100w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-135.jpg 135w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-160.jpg 160w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-180.jpg 180w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-200.jpg 200w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-270.jpg 270w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-320.jpg 320w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/royaume-uni/67564ebe212d33.53018434-360.jpg 360w"
            sizes ="(min-width: 800px) 180px, (min-width: 700px) 25vw, 50vw" 
            alt="1 Penny - Victoria (2nd portrait; 1st type) -  obverse" />
    </a>
        <p class="mentions">&copy; DMK Collection</p>
        


    <h3>Mint</h3>
    <a href="mint.php?id=17">Royal Mint (Tower Hill)</a>, London, United Kingdom (1810-1975)

    <h3>Comments</h3>
    <div id="fiche_comments" class="ck-content"><p>The standard weight of these pieces was 48 to the pound avoirdupois (1/3 ounce or 145.8 grains).<br><br>There are many obverse and reverse varieties for this type, following is a selection of them:<br><br><strong>Sp#3954</strong> <i>(1860-1894)</i> no mintmark on reverse;<br><strong>Sp#3955</strong> <i>(1874/5/6, 1881/2)</i> 'H' mintmark on reverse below date, struck at Ralph Heaton &amp; Sons, Birmingham.<br><br>In 1874, the second portrait was very slightly changed. In KM#749, the D:G: is closer to the Queen's head.<br>So take care if you have an 1874 in case it is KM#755.<br><br><strong>KM#749.1</strong> <i>(1860 only)</i> Beaded border, without die number;<br><strong>KM#749.2</strong> <i>(1860-1874)</i> Toothed border, without die number;<br><strong>KM#749.3</strong> <i>(1863 only)</i> Toothed border, with die number below date;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6957df5f03259.jpg" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="forum488960907"><img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6957df5f03259.jpg"></a><br><br>There are many other small variations to the obverse and reverse designs, all full list of which can be found (with pictures) in the latest version of the Spink Standard Catalogue of British Coins.<br><br>How to count number of leaves on the wreath:<br><br><a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/67a3bc3684858.png" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="forum488960907"><img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/67a3bc3684858.png"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sometimes, the striking process and excessive wear make it difficult to differentiate the 1860 beads and denticles varieties. The following illustrations should help:</p><p><a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/68b3202472d0e.jpg" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="forum488960907"><img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/68b3202472d0e.jpg"></a> <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/68b3202f8d7ce.jpg" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="forum488960907"><img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/68b3202f8d7ce.jpg"></a></p></div>
    <script>
        const comment_collapsed_height = 30; // in em
        const $comment_box = $('#fiche_comments');
        if ($comment_box.height() > comment_collapsed_height * 1.20 * 16) {
            $comment_box
                .addClass('collapsed')
                .css('height', comment_collapsed_height + 'em') // defined here rather than in CSS to allow height animation
                .after('<button id="fiche_comments_toggle" class="secondary">Read more</button>');
            $('#fiche_comments_toggle').click(function() {
                if ($comment_box.hasClass('collapsed')) {
                    $comment_box.removeClass('collapsed').css('height', $comment_box.prop('scrollHeight') + 'px');
                    $('#fiche_comments_toggle').text('Show less');
                }
                else {
                    $comment_box.addClass('collapsed').css('height', comment_collapsed_height + 'em');
                    $('#fiche_comments_toggle').text('Read more');
                    // scroll back to the comments only if needed
                    const bottom_of_collapsed_comments = $comment_box.offset().top + comment_collapsed_height * 16;
                    if ($([document.documentElement, document.body]).scrollTop() > bottom_of_collapsed_comments) {
                        $([document.documentElement, document.body]).animate({ scrollTop: bottom_of_collapsed_comments * 0.95 }, 500);
                    }
                }
            });
        }
        else {
            $comment_box.css('position', 'initial') // avoid cropping coin thumbnails
        }
    </script>


