                            An example of year 1862.<br />
The official weight of the coin should be 9.45 grams.<br />
This example coin weighs a little more, possibly due to rust and some dirt. It is worth noting that it also comes from a marine coastal city where it was where it was stored for many years (Some rust can be seen on the patina)<br />
The diameter of this example coin matches the official one of 30.86 mm.                        </div>
